<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,978,2017]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1920,1945]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species also belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[690,821,1920,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albisquama">
<emphasis box="[690,821,1920,1945]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">albisquama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, and its distiphallus is somewhat similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[187,506,1956,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinuliloba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[187,506,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Melanagromyza spinuliloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[518,613,1956,1981]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[518,544,1956,1981]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[564,606,1956,1981]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the spinulose patch on the distiphallus. But, the expanded basiphallic sclerites of this species are unique among the congenerous species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1225,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[199,1225,151,176]" box="[199,1225,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specifc name refers to the swollen (Latin: 
<emphasis box="[862,954,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">turgidus</emphasis>
) basiphallic membrane.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
